Came to CIRCA for happy hour on a Thursday, and they have these delicious Bulgogi Lettuce Wraps for $2 each! They also have other happy hour deals, but I only ordered the lettuce wraps.  The good: The Bulgogi Lettuce Wrap was delicious! It contains marainted short rib, bibb lettuce, sticky rice, kimchi aioli, chopped peanuts, and micro cilantro. The sauce was creamy, and I enjoyed the savory beef, and all the ingredients well really well together! Will definitely come back to order more.  The bad: The server should have been a bit more clear because he said the whole dish was $2, and not $2 each. Even though the deal sounded too good to be true, it is a Thursday only deal, so I just went along with it without asking for clarification until I received the bill.  Overall, I really enjoyed the Bulgogi Lettuce Wrap, and I'll be returning just to eat more of this! Definitely worth it for $2 each!

Really good food. The Bruscetta was amazing.  We had Bruscetta, Crab Cakes, a Dark Chocolate Tort and some chicken. The fries with the crab cakes were literally perfect. Just enough salt, loud crispy outside with a soft inside. If I'm being honest, they were better than the crab cakes themselves (which were also good and very light).  The chicken was optimally juicy. The tort was good.  The Bruscetta was the best part of the meal though. That bread was also perfect. The oil and cheese was super delicious and we'll definetely be getting that same Bruscetta when we come back. I wish I could just order 3 of the Bruscetta and call that a meal.  Wait staff is nice. We did come on a Sunday when it wasn't busy though. Décor is top notch. Music was just a tinsy bit too loud for me, but my girlfriend thinks it was just fine.  Totally recommend.

Overpriced but okay food, downright awful service.  Put in a reservation for 4, when we arrived they didn't have it in their system it then when I showed them the call record they suddenly found it.  We were seated and immediately the manager hit me with his rear end hard enough for me to splash my water.  I turned my head up at him and he gave me a "what're you looking at?" face.  Still not sure who our waitress was, after about 15 minutes of waiting we witnessed an at-the-table debate of "is this one yours or mine?" We put in our drink orders then waited about 25 minutes for 2 beers and 2 glasses of wine. We had to put in our food orders before our first round came and tell them to bring out the check because we were running late now.  When the food came out our friend ordered the steak frites medium and it came out blue rare. Another friend ordered an app and a side as an entree, one was missing the prosciutto and the other was missing the bacon.  My jambalaya was fine, but as my partner said, "it tasted like a jambalaya inspired italian pasta."  Finally when it came time to pay we asked to use part of a gift card I'd gotten from work then split the rest evenly between 2 cards.  That didn't happen and my friend and his partner ended up getting the Lions share of the check put on their card despite ordering less.  It's a shame because I've been here for take out and happy hour and it's a perfectly fine spot for a drink or a bite on the go, but I am absolutely embarrassed I recommended we go here for dinner after the service we received.

I came here recently for my birthday dinner with a large party (10 people). I placed a reservation about a week in advance and I was glad that I discovered this location! It was difficult to find a restaurant in DC that was able to accommodate a larger group on shorter notice, and we were all seated comfortably at Circa at Chinatown. This is closeby to the metro stop so it was convenient to get to. We were seated upstairs and had a long table with a booth/bench on one side and chairs on the other side. We ordered drinks and appetizers while we were waiting on a few people from our party to arrive. The Shotgun Shrimp appetizer that I got was delicious, and featured large pieces of shrimp. Other people in my party got the recommended Bulgogi Lettuce Wraps which was delicious as well. For my entree, I got the Seared Scallops (came with 3 scallops) which came with a creamy mushroom risotto, basil oil, and saba drizzle. The entree was on the pricier side, especially for the smaller portion for the food, but the taste made up for the price. Towards the end of the dinner, the staff there provided me a birthday card signed with all of their names which was a kind gesture. They also offered a dessert on the house, which I ended up picking the Brioche Bread Pudding which was delicious. The hot and cold temperatures of the bread pudding and the ice cream complemented each other perfectly and was a delicious dessert. I would definitely come back again if I am taking someone out for a nice dinner out in DC.

Making a reservation here was easy. The restaurant is located in the busy part of Chinatown right near the Metro, so I was initially worried about the volume of the street at dinner, but you literally couldn't tell that you are on a busy street. The restaurant portion of this place is upstairs and it's pretty spacious.  I started with the Roseberry Smash with Tito's. Wow, this drink was good. It was refreshing and crisp and also had a hint of jalapeño for some spice to it. I would definitely order it again.  We started with the calamari which was an excellent choice. The batter was light and the dipping sauce was perfectly spicy. It seems like Circa is really good at finding flavors that complement each other very well and this dish was exceptional.  After the drink and the calamari I was kind of full so I ordered the appetizer brussel sprouts for my main meal. They were AWESOME, with a hint of blue cheese at the bottom of the pan which was great with the thick cut bacon.  My friend ordered the fried chicken sandwich and said he enjoyed it!  Service was so friendly and our waitress was super patient with us despite the fact that we talked for a while and were there for quite some time.  I can not recommend this place enough, and I'm so glad it's in my neighborhood!
The drinks are amazing. The Purple Rain drink is a flood of different tastes and is by far my favorite. The food has been delicious every time I have been in. Great service as well.

The facelift provided to this place from the former Zengo layout to current is amazing. The flavors in the food was perfect. The crabcake had a hint of spice, that gave them a little kick. If you are a person like myself that has to be visually drawn in by food before you can eat it, then this place is for you. The plates were well plated. The crabcakes were a little smaller than expected compared to other places in the area that are about on the same scale. However, I was provided with an additional crabcake. The pickles on the plate tasted as if they were done in house and were perfectly flavored. The service was very attentive and amazing across the board. The menu was a little displacing but had something for everyone and I appreciated the inclusiveness of it.  If you are looking for a location that is stunning to the eye, good energy vibe, and great service. At the end the check came fast and the prices were very reasonable. This is a highly recommended place! I will be back to try the happy hour with my team soon.
